Physical Topology
Once all three routers were configured we connected them into the hub-and-spoke layout. The wall outlet goes into the CBD router WAN port. The Clayton and Mernda routers each connect their WAN port into one of the CBD router LAN ports. Each router then connects to its Cisco Catalyst 3560-CX switch, which connects to the end device. This matches the design we built in Packet Tracer.

Router Security Hardening
We went into each router admin panel and made the following changes on all three:

Changed the default admin password
Set wireless security to WPA2-PSK with AES encryption
Renamed each SSID to match the campus name (CBD campus, Clayton campus, Mernda campus)
Turned off remote management

