Known Limitations
Pinging end devices across campuses returned destination host unreachable. This happens because the TP-Link routers are consumer-grade devices doing NAT. Traffic behind each router cannot be reached directly from another subnet without static routes or enterprise routing equipment. This is a hardware limitation not a design problem. The Packet Tracer simulation already shows full end-to-end connectivity under proper enterprise conditions.
VLAN separation across campuses is handled by Windows Firewall ACL rules on the VM rather than inter-switch trunking. Full trunking between campuses would need enterprise-grade inter-campus switching.

